This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with cross-lingual natural language processing tasks such as textual entailment and event coreference. Additionally, the paper proposes an unsupervised approach for learning bilingual word embeddings based on dependency contexts, which is a common technique used in NLP. 

The paper also involves machine learning techniques, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). 

Furthermore, the paper involves information retrieval techniques, as it deals with detecting hypernymy relationships between words, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.IR (Information Retrieval). 

Finally, the paper involves the creation of a dataset, which suggests that it could belong to the sub-category of cs.SD (Sound and Music Computing, Information Retrieval, and Signal Processing).
